      "content": "A robust, well-defended line of argument centers on national sovereignty and the rule of law. Stricter enforcement is not about hostility; it is about maintaining the integrity of the nation's legal framework, which is the bedrock of a stable society. Furthermore, increased funding is a necessary investment to prevent transnational criminal organizations from exploiting porous borders to traffic drugs and human beings. A secure border is a prerequisite for domestic safety and economic predictability.",
