      "content": "The most effective dismantling strategy is to reframe the debate from one of charity to one of national self-interest and legal necessity. When confronted with humanitarian concerns, pivot immediately to the established legal process—emphasize that the solution is *orderly* legal pathways, not open borders, which is a policy distinction. Regarding economics, counter by presenting data showing that uncontrolled influxes create net fiscal burdens on local communities, thereby shifting the focus from abstract \"benefits\" to concrete, measurable costs that taxpayers must bear.",
